mlx-swift-ml-sharp
===================

This project is a Swift / mlx-swift port of:

    ml-sharp — Apple's reference implementation of SHARP, a feed-forward
    3D Gaussian splat predictor from a single image.
    https://github.com/apple/ml-sharp

The original Python implementation and the SHARP model architecture are
copyright (C) 2025 Apple Inc. and are licensed under the Apple Sample Code
License (see LICENSE) and, for the model weights, the Apple Machine Learning
Research Model License (see LICENSE_MODEL).

The Swift port — including the mlx-swift module structure under
`Sources/MLXSharp/`, the model-weight conversion script under `scripts/`,
the example macOS application under `Examples/MLXSharpApp/`, and the test
fixtures under `Tests/` — is copyright (C) 2026 Hiroaki Yamane and is
distributed under the same Apple Sample Code License as the upstream
Python project.

The Swift port is functionally and numerically equivalent to the upstream
Python implementation: every non-rotation field of the exported `.ply` matches
Python's reference output within float-precision noise on the same input.
Quaternion sign conventions differ between LAPACK (Swift) and torch.linalg.svd
(Python) for the same covariance — this is mathematically equivalent and
visually invariant, not a port-correctness gap.

